WHAT TODAY'S RELIGIOUS HOLIDAY
05 Nov 2019, 21:00 by Leitz Natalia

Today, November 6, marks International Day for the Prevention of Exploitation of the Environment during War and Armed Conflict and Saxophone Day. To your attention the traditions and signs of this day - learn what can and cannot be done!

The date of November 6th is a history of several significant events and holidays.
According to the church calendar, believers today celebrate the day of the miraculous image of Our Lady of All Sorrows Joy. This icon became known for healing believers from many ailments. Also, those who have a lot of sadness go to it
NAME: WHO'S ANGEL'S DAY CELEBRATION
On Wednesday, November 6th, the names of the names will be celebrated by the holders of the following names: Athanasius, Athanasius, Heraclius, George, Peter, Ivan, Olesia, Alexander and Nicholas. Do not forget to congratulate the culprits of the holiday with angel's day!



THIS DAY IN HISTORY: INTERNATIONAL HOLIDAYS AND EVENTS

1860 - Abraham Lincoln is elected the 16th President of the United States of America
1944 - Kyiv radio station was restored and restored.
1951 - Kyiv Professional Television Center started operating on Khreschatyk Street, 26, so this day is considered the beginning of the history of Ukrainian television.
1960 - the first stage of the subway started operating in Kyiv - the 5-kilometer section of the Svyatoshino-Brovarsk line connected the stations of Vokzalnaya, University, Khreshchatyk, Arsenalna, Dnipro;
1962 - The UN General Assembly adopts a resolution condemning the racist policies of apartheid in the Republic of South Africa and urges all UN members to end any economic and military relations with South Africa.
1980 - a new Ingul Bridge was built in Nikolaev, the length of the bridge was 485 m.
1984 - Republican Ronald Reagan wins a convincing victory for the second time in the US presidential election;

1987 - 28th subway station was opened in Kiev - Lenin (now Teatralna)

1991 - The Communist Party of the Soviet Union dissolved
1999 - In Australia, 54.5% of voters oppose the country's proclamation, once again recognizing as the formal head of state of the British monarch.





WHO WAS BORN ON NOVEMBER 6

1771 - Alois Zenefelder, inventor of lithography.
1811 - Markian Shashkevich, Ukrainian writer, poet, cultural and public figure, head of the Russian Trinity;
1814 - Adolf Sachs, Belgian master of wind instruments, inventor of saxophone;
1855 - Dmytro Yavornitsky, Ukrainian historian, Cossack researcher, archeologist, ethnographer, folklorist, writer, academician of the USSR Academy of Sciences (1923).
1860 - Ignatius Jan Paderewski, Polish virtuoso pianist, composer, politician;
1861 - James Naismith, Canadian physical education teacher, inventor of basketball (1891);
1880 - Robert Musil, an Austrian writer and essayist, playwright and theater critic.
1931 - Mike Nichols (Michael Peshkovsky), American director, Oscar winner;
1936 - Bras Yosyp Emmanuilovich, Ukrainian painter and graphic artist.
1938 - Vladimir Zharykov, Ukrainian actor, stuntman. He has appeared in the films: Hate, Pirates of the XX Century, The Meeting Place Cannot Be Changed, Ten Black Men and Others.
1952 - Michael Cunningham is an American writer.

1988 - Emma Stone, American actress.

1988 - Conchita Wurst, Austrian singer, Eurovision 2014 winner.





If you break the mirror on November 6, you should expect misery;
If a white dog is running after a person today, he represents happiness as it should appear in life;
If there are many crows in the sky, it will soon snow;
If you hear the crows crow, you should expect a blizzard and a cold.




WHAT CAN'T DO TODAY

You cannot do heavy physical labor;
You cannot swear and quarrel with your surroundings;
You can not walk in the night and abuse alcohol;
Cannot be addicted to bad habits;
You cannot do homework and the city.


